  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6604.34 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6609 and maximum positive gamma at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any rally attempt into the 6605-6610 zone where massive +53-52B gamma walls create heavy resistance. The PIN regime with 145B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting flows, while the recent gex_surge event indicates dealers just accumulated significant long gamma positions that will dampen volatility. Watch 6590 as the critical support level where negative gamma kicks in (-28B) and dealer buying would accelerate any breakdown, but the thick positive gamma cushion above should cap upside momentum.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6610 with muted volatility.",
